<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-028-572  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 028 572.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Jan 8 1990 v6 n1 p37(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DacEasy upgrade answers needs of larger firms. (Software Review)(DacEasy Accounting 4.0; First Look) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Vyvial, Ronald E.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Dallas-based DacEasy Inc debuts the $149.95 DacEasy Accounting 4.0software package.andP;  Enhancements include the ability to accommodatesales histories, back orders, multi-tiered pricing, recurringtransactions and alternative vendors.andP;  A major improvement inversion 4.0 is the ability to create a database from invoicedetails for tracking sales by customer.andP;  Version 4.0 also booststhe data field lengths of most files and includes features fromDacEasy's Graph+Mate report writer and utility package.andP;  Version4.0's handling of back orders is problematic.andP;  New Assembly andRepetitive Transaction modules reduce repetitive data entry.andO;Version 4.0 is faster, thanks to a new approach to file indexingand faster processing times for posting routines.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   DacEasy Inc. (products).andO;Product:   DacEasy Accounting 4.0 (Accounting software).andO;Topic:     EvaluationAccountingSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Ronald E. VyvialandM;To address the needs of large companies, DacEasy Inc. has released version4.0 of its flagship product, DacEasy Accounting.andM;The package now can accommodate multitiered pricing, customer saleshistories, back orders, recurring transactions and alternative vendors.andP;  Inaddition, the $149.95 package offers increased data field lengths in mostfiles and incorporates features from the firm's Graph+Mate report writer andutility package, which used to be optional.andM;The package's support for multitiered pricing is a welcome addition.andP;  It nowhandles volume discounts, discounts to various customer groups or acombination of the two.andP;  Also, the billing system can accommodate flexiblepricing alternatives and incentives.andM;One of the greatest weaknesses of DacEasy Accounting has been its inabilityto track product or service sales by customer.andP;  Version 4.0 now allows theuser to create a database from invoice details.andP;  This database is availableto the report writer, allowing virtually any analysis imaginable.andM;Back orders -- an annoyance to most businesses -- receive much attention, butnever seem to be under control.andP;  While the new invoice database now allowssummarization of back-ordered items by product or customer, reports fail torecap revenue outstanding from such items.andM;Many businesses will appreciate the new Assembly and Repetitive Transactionmodules, which help reduce repetitive data entry.andP;  Improved purchasinginformation is also available.andP;  Along with indicating basic information -- alow stock condition, a reorder quantity and a vendor -- each product recordcan specify two alternative vendors and their part numbers for the product.andM;Users of earlier DacEasy Accounting versions either had to make do withrudimentary built-in reporting functions or purchase the Graph+Mate package.andO;Version 4.0 now incorporates many of Graph+Mate's features, and in some casesexpands on them.andP;  The report writer's sort/selection criteria have beenincreased from one to three.andP;  And, while users once had to download to aspreadsheet to refine reports, the program now offers full reportingcapabilities.andM;All of these added features do not slow the package down: A new approach tofile indexing has made a noticeable improvement in its response time.andP;  Also,posting routines can be processed much more quickly than in the past.andM;Registered users can upgrade to 4.0 for $60.andM;DacEasy Inc. can be reached in Dallas at (214) 248-0305.andM;----------Ronald E. Vyvial is a financial and data-operations administrator for a smallmanufacturing firm in Texas.andO;</TEXT></DOC>